Lonmin, Sappi Shares May Move: South African Equity Preview

-- B y   M i k e   C o h e n
-- 
2011-05-09T04:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-08/lonmin-sappi-shares-may-move-south-african-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or fall
in  South Africa . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are from
the last close.  South Africa’s FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index rose 296.69,
or 0.9 percent, to 31,878.83 in Johannesburg.  Lonmin Plc (LMI)  : The third-largest platinum producer
releases first-half earnings. The shares fell 80 cents, or 0.5
percent, to 170.10 rand.  Sappi Ltd. (SPP)  : The world’s largest producer of glossy
magazine paper releases earnings for the three months through
March. Sappi climbed 25 cents, or 0.7 percent, to 34.65 rand.  The following shares begin trading without the rights to
their latest dividends:  Brimstone Investments Corp. (BRN SJ), Cipla Medpro South
Africa Ltd. (CMP SJ), Country Bird Holdings Ltd. (CBH SJ), IQuad
Group Ltd. (IQG SJ) and PSG Group Ltd. (PSG SJ).  Shares or American depositary receipts of the following
South African companies closed as follows:  Anglo American Plc (AAUKY)   increased 3.2 percent to
$24.74. AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (AU US) fell 0.3 percent to
$45.65. BHP Billiton Ltd. (BBL US) rose 1.5 percent to $78.76.
 DRDGold Ltd. (DROOY)   fell 0.4 percent to $5.20. Gold Fields
Ltd. (GFI US) rose 0.1 percent to $15.92. Harmony Gold Mining
Co. (HMY US) gained 1.5 percent to $13.91. Impala Platinum
Holdings (IMPUY US) rose 2.8 percent to $27.65.  Sappi Ltd. (SAP)   was unchanged at $5.05.  Sasol Ltd. (SSL)   climbed 2.5
percent to $53.25.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mike Cohen in  Cape Town  at 
 mcohen21@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Barden at   barden@bloomberg.net . 